						<summary>

						<p>This consists of twenty disjointed fragmentary pieces uniting (probably of more than one inscription). The introduction is that of Rājādhirāja I beginning with the expressions <hi rend="italic">Tiṅgaḷēr taru</hi> etc. The inscription seems to record a gift of money by a private individual for burning a lamp in the temple of Mūlasthānamuḍaiyār, and the purchase of some land tax-free with that amount (by the temple) from the assembly of the place.</p>						

						</summary>
